%I A394060 #8 Mar 15 2026 18:46:57
%S A394060 1,3,7,11,15,23,27,35,43,47,51,59,63,75,87,95,103,107,111,119,127,131,
%T A394060 135,151,155,163,167,171,183,191,195,211,215,223,227,231,247,255,271,
%U A394060 275,287,295,303,311,315,339,347,351,367,371,379,383,387,399,415,423
%N A394060 a(n+1) = a(n) + 2*d(a(n)) if s(a(n)) <= a(n), else 2*a(n) - s(a(n)), with a(1) = 1; d(k) is the number of divisors of k A000005 and s(k) is the aliquot sum of k A001065.
%C A394060 The sequence becomes periodic starting from a(898)
%C A394060 Starting with a(1) = 2 instead of 1 yields the prefix 2, 6, 14, 22, 30, 18, 15, after which the sequence merges with the current terms starting from a(8) = 23 (which corresponds to a(6) of the main sequence).
%H A394060 Adam Karol Drażyk, <a href="/A394060/b394060.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000</a>
%F A394060 a(n+1) = if s(a(n)) <= a(n) then a(n) + 2*d(a(n)) else 2*a(n) - s(a(n)), where s(k) is A001065(k) and d(k) is A000005(k).
%e A394060 Starting with a(1) = 1.
%e A394060 Sum of proper divisors of 1 is less than 1, so 1 + 2 * d(1) = 1 + 2 * 0 = 3. So a(2) = 3.
%e A394060 Sum of proper divisors of 3 is less than 3, so 3 + 2 * d(3) = 3 + 2 * 2 = 7. So a(3) = 7
%e A394060 Sum of proper divisors of 7 is less than 7, so 7 + 2 * d(7) = 7 + 2 * 2 = 11. So a(4) = 11.
%e A394060 Sum of proper divisors of 11 is less than 11, so 11 + 2 * d(1) = 1 + 2 * 2 = 15. So a(5) = 15.
%e A394060 Sum of proper divisors of 15 is less than 15, so 15 + 2 * d(15) = 15 + 2 * 4 = 23. So a(6) = 23.
%t A394060 NestWhileList[
%t A394060  If[DivisorSigma[1, #] <= 2*#, # + 2*DivisorSigma[0, #],
%t A394060    3*# - DivisorSigma[1, #]] &, 1, Unequal, All]
%Y A394060 Cf. A000005, A001065, A392092 (different initial values).
%K A394060 nonn
%O A394060 1,2
%A A394060 _Adam Karol Drażyk_, Mar 09 2026
